### Slots

| Name | Props | Description |
|------|------|------|
| `empty` | - | Custom fallback content when neither `icon` nor `name` resolves to a visible icon. |

### Events

`TuffIcon`, `TxIcon`, and `TxStatusIcon` do not emit events.

## Rendering Contract

- `name` values starting with `i-` render as icon classes; known built-in names render as `builtin` SVG.
- `file` and local absolute `url` values can be transformed by injected `fileProtocol` or `urlResolver`.
- SVG uses a `currentColor` mask when `colorful=false`; `colorful=true` or `icon.colorful=true` renders the original image.
- `status='loading' | 'error'` takes precedence over normal icon rendering.

## Best Practices

- Prefer UnoCSS class icons (`i-*`) for product UI because they are cheap to render and inherit `currentColor`.
- Use `TxIconSource` when the source needs status, color, URL/file resolution, or original SVG colors.
- Pass meaningful `alt` only when the icon itself carries meaning. Decorative icons should be paired with visible text or hidden by surrounding semantics.
- Keep `colorful=false` for monochrome SVGs so theme color can flow through `currentColor`; set `colorful=true` for brand marks and multi-color artwork.
- Inject `TX_ICON_CONFIG_KEY` once at the app shell when resolving plugin files or custom SVG transports, instead of passing resolvers to every icon.

## Icon sets

| Set | Prefix | Description |
|-----|--------|-------------|
| Remix Icon | `i-ri-` | General UI icons, outline/filled styles |
| Carbon | `i-carbon-` | IBM design system icons |
| Simple Icons | `i-simple-icons-` | Brand/logo icons |

