## API Reference

### classIcon / getIcon

::TuffCodeBlock{lang="ts"}
---
code: |
  import { classIcon, getIcon } from '@talex-touch/utils'

  const icon = classIcon('i-ri-star-line')
  // { type: 'class', value: 'i-ri-star-line' }

  const searchIcon = getIcon('Search')
  // { type: 'class', value: 'i-ri-search-line' }
---
::


## Review Notes

- **Accessibility note:** `TxIcon` sets `role="img"` and maps `alt` to `title`; icon-only interactive controls should use `TxIconButton label` or visible text instead of relying on icon title text alone.
- **Verified coverage:** `icon.test.ts` verifies class and built-in name rendering, size/color styles, emoji/empty/loading/error states, injected file protocol resolution, SVG mask mode, colorful SVG fallback, data SVG handling, multi-color SVG detection, and status indicator sizing.

## Source

- Component sources: `packages/tuffex/packages/components/src/icon/src/TxIcon.vue` and `TxStatusIcon.vue`.
- Types/helpers: `types.ts` exports `TxIconSource`, status/config types, and `TX_ICON_CONFIG_KEY`; `svg-color-mode.ts` decides whether an SVG can render as a currentColor mask.
- Export aliases: `packages/tuffex/packages/components/src/icon/index.ts` exports `TuffIcon`, `TxIcon`, `TxStatusIcon`, `TX_ICON_CONFIG_KEY`, icon types, and `shouldRenderSvgAsMask`.
- Coverage: `packages/tuffex/packages/components/src/icon/__tests__/icon.test.ts` covers icon source resolution, SVG color-mode behavior, status states, injected config, and status overlays.

